title: israel
text: Great tour on a modern bus. Had enough time for our needs and a bit of free time at each site. Loved all the sites.
place: Unforgettable Tour to Caesarea, Haifa, Acre and Rosh HaNikra from Tel Aviv

title: sunset views
text: great for sunset views if you can be there for sunset. The house next door that has a tour of some misallocated European is only some what interesting. The restraint seems very over priced.

title: San Jose
text: Nice flight. Served breakfast and lunch on the way. Also had a few compliment Ron Abuelo's when they came through with the drink cart.

title: Cathedrale
text: Great history and a highly rated favorite of my of my visit to Antibes. It is next to the museum and should not be missed if you are into old churches or religious sites.
place: Cathedrale Notre Dame de la Platea d'Antibes

title: Antibes
text: Interesting place to visit. Visit to old section was nice but did not do the museum next to the church. Nice stroll through the market and walk along the city walls.
place: Private 4-hour Tour of Cannes and Antibes from Cannes with private driver

title: Walk about
text: We just did our own thing. Had a wonderful time exploring all the nooks and niches of the area. Nice museum with a lot of different advantages the one nearest the Parthenon does not have due to location.

title: Have to do at least once
text: A wondrous adventure. Why would you not do this at least once after going all the way to Athens. The weather was good when we went the first week in November. It deteriorated from then on. Many places seemed to be closed for the season at this time and/or it could be the day we were there.

title: loud
text:
I stayed in unit 3 on the 4th floor. The construction of the unit is very poor. The bathroom door only opens about 75% of the way due to a beam running on the ceiling. There is a central metal trash dumpster on the corner below the unit. There is no sound damping between the unit that shares a window with this unit. The person in unit 4 was talking on the phone, it sounded like he was standing next to our bed. This unit shares a large plate glass window with unit 4 and there is a space between where the wall ends against the window of about 1/2" Some one could easy slip a spy camera into that space. Bags of bottles are being dropped into the metal trash container late at night after the business close and early in the morning, 05:00- 05:30, a large truck comes buy to pic up the container and deliver an empty one. There is also a high pressure water compressor they use to wash the area every morning. You might as well be sleeping in the street noise wise.

On the positive side, good location and nice common area with all the stuff you need except ear plugs.

title: Romanian Air
text: Older plane, on time and good service by staff. Cheapest flight from TLV to Athens via a short layover in Romania.

title: Interesting
text: Nice day visit with friendly native people. Great beach and snorkel opportunity. Did some site seeing of the island and sampled the local cuisine.

title: What a dive!
text: Great experience. The trip out was rough due to rough seas for a lot of people but once out on the reef every one recovered quickly. Spent 3 days and two nights on the reef. You can rent a camera for underwater (higher pixel count then the sale camera) use or buy a camera on the ship. I rented one for one day and am pleased with the results. Used the stinger suit.

title: Refreshing surprize
text: A pleasant fresh water cave experience. It is a little difficult to get in and out of the water and the electric bulb does help quite a bit to see what you are doing. Pay with Australian dollars and not American dollrs.

title: Quirky
text: Interesting and unexpected find. They supply bug spray and a local guide that shows you around and answers questions. We were lucky and only the two of us were in the English speaking group, so we had a private tour!

title: Deep snork
text: We did 3 days 2 nights snorkeling on the reef from Cairns. A good dive site may not be a good snorkeling site and a good snorkeling spot may not be a good dive site.They did a good job of moving around to provided opportunities that were well balanced to accommodate both divers and snorkelers. I did not at any time feel that they favored one over the other and realize that diving offers better opportunities on the reef than snorkeling. Saw sharks, rays, schools of fish, many types reef fish, many of coral and, yes; I did find Nimo. The live a board accommodations were better than I was expecting. I would rate the food at a 60%. It was a fun experience enhanced by a professional crew and I would do it again if I find myself in Cairns.
place: Great Barrier Reef Diving and Snorkeling Cruise from Cairns

title: eats
text: Ate outside at the tables. Generous portions, friendly service and good price for what you get. I would eat there again.

title: Cairns
text: What a wonderful aquarium. Has two supper fantastic large tanks with a great reef display and lots of smaller tanks that are common to aquariums. The biggest tank that has many viewing opportunities from massive windows to tunnels.

title: garden
text: Really nice. Free. easy to get to by bus or foot. Lots to see at besides the formal garden. It will take all day to see everything in the "precinct".

title: cairns
text: Stayed one night. Nice dip pool next to common area. Well stocked common kitchen with micro, stove, refrigerator and dishwasher. No elevator for second floor units. Friendly family feel to motel and within walking distance to main attractions.

title: pizza
text: Great place to get a real garlic based pizza sauce. Great wait staff and fast service in a historic building.

title: real
text: They have a fantastic veggie burger, Home made, never frozen and tastes great. Directly across from the fire dept. and has patio sitting in the back. Best veggie burger I ever had,

title: Delighful
text: We went for the buffet and was pleasantly surprised. Lots of vegan and non-vegan to chose from. Some of the food may be considered spicy by American standards but there was also some mildly spiced food on the buffet as well. Located in a nice old building in the down town area. Fresh hot Nan a standard. Even though we were using the buffet, we were given great service. I will be going back.

title: Mo MO
text: Was looking fore ward to a good MoMo. The fillings were very Americanized, bland compared to Nepal street food, But, it does give you an idea of what MO MO is. I liked the different kinds they have but they are bland compared to the real thing. Only one sauce instead of the two in Nepal. These are also spiced down. The Nan was Good. Mo Mo is a big thing in Nepal, Nepal fast street food, cooked on the spot and fresh.

title: Really nice
text: Close to everything, walking distance, in Istanbul. The tramway stop is only a few blocks away. Super friendly staff and happy to accommodate. Nice breakfast buffet style. I would stay again at this reasonably priced hotel.

title: Nice experience
text: Walked acrossd twice to and from Galanta Tower after a short tramway ride from the Hotel. Restaurants were pressed for first customers, lower level, and offered discounts. Great bridge to fish from and view of native culture.

title: Have to do
text: You would be missing a major attraction unique to Istanbul. A few stops along the way and you can swim in the Black Sea.

title: Do not miss
text: Wonderful view of the Bosphorus Straight and a highly educational experience. Walked there from the Hotel Antea.

title: Short. but do not miss.
text: Interesting history. There are many Cisterns but this is the best to date. If you can only see one, do this one. There is a Cistern across from the Antea Hotel but it is still/was being renovated at time of visit.

title: Central
text: This is the area I stayed in. It was close to all the major attractions, short walking distance. A great place to explore out side of guided tours. People were eager to help you find what you are looking for.

title: awsome
text: Some renovation going on to restore it to it's proper significance in Istanbul's history. Do not miss this historical site and do your homework before visiting.

title: walked
text: Took the Tramway from the hotel over the bridge and did the tunnel up to Galata tower. Great views to say the least. Walked back to the hotel after having lunch under the bridge via the Bazaar, spice market past Hagia Sophia. This area is a tourists dream come true.

title: great view
text: Nice piece of history. Easy climb for a good view. Well worth the effort. Make sure you take the tunnel up to enhance your experience. You can walk down hill to the bridge past all the shops.

title: The best
text: They picked up and delivered you to the Airport at no charge. Why would you stay in the noisy city/airport when you can escape to a quite game lodge. There are a few stores 1.7 kl/ one mile, from the lodge. They pick up and drop off on the hour when I was there. The pick up point at that time was at the information booth as soon as you clear the baggage area. Spent three nights, not continues, service was excellent. I would do it again.

title: fly dry
text: Not used to flying dry. First international flight I have taken that did not have liquor on board. I was disappointed I could not have my usual night cap to help fall asleep. Stayed awake the whole time.

title: Dry flight
text: Another dry overnight flight. No beer, wine or liquer on this flight from Joberg to Cairo and from Cairo to JFK.

title: Normal international flight
text: Above normal flight for an international trip. They had great service, beer, liquor and wine. The food served was a little above average for flight food.

title: big bus
text: Just what you would expect for a big American bus in the sky. The usual tiny bag of pretzels and a soft drink.

title: I would do it again
text: Great service, complementary drinks, served food on booth short flights and the flight was not crowed. Older plane but in good shape.

title: Fast
text: Quick and Fast overnight flight to JFK. Basic service for an American airline. It's a ( like southwest) long haul economy line. You can pick your seat ahead of time.

title: Wet and Wild
text: Stayed at N-1 hotel. It is within walking distance to the Falls and next to a major craft market. Breakfast was cheep and the bottomless cup of, instant, coffee was great at breakfast. There are a few grocery stores within walking distance as well as several eating establishments. The Post office is on the corner. I liked Ma Ma Africa, just across the railroad tracks, and went twice. Some nights they have local musicians playing.
